          "extensions": [],
          "experiment_extension_reason": "Preventing Partner Disruption: Extending the trial ensures key partners (like Zoom, Cisco, Meet, Search) retain this improved 'Use precise location' functionality until the full rollout.\n\nValidating at Scale: A higher page load limit allows high-traffic partners to scale their successful implementations, validating positive results across a wider audience and mitigating risks before the full M143 launch.\n\nEnabling New, High-Impact Experimentation: The increased limit is necessary to:\n\nValidate PEPC's integration with the upcoming Approximate Location feature.\n\nGather statistically significant data across multiple UI test variations for the new user flow (Approximate ↔ Precise location change) to build the best experience.\n\nNew Experimentation Plan: The extension provides a bridge to future API changes, as learnings from the current trial (including Approximate Location experiments) will directly inform the launch of the new <geolocation> element in M143. User Media (Camera/Mic) will get a separate Origin Trial.",
          "ot_stage_id": 5103160636473344,
